# SCAS

22 localhost-only supply-chain attack labs (`scenarios/01-`…`22-`). Docs hub: `documentation/index.md` — `docs/` is a GitHub Pages mirror; do not edit both.

## Safety (never weaken)

- `setup.sh` sources `scenarios/_shared/enable-testbench.sh`
- Payloads gate on `TESTBENCH_MODE === 'enabled'` before malicious paths
- Exfil targets `127.0.0.1` / `localhost` only

## Canonical examples (read one, grep the rest)

| Need | Path |
|------|------|
| Mock server | `scenarios/01-typosquatting/infrastructure/mock-server.js` |
| New mock server | `scenarios/_shared/mock-server-template.js` |
| Setup | `scenarios/01-typosquatting/setup.sh` |
| Payload template | `scenarios/01-typosquatting/templates/malicious-package-template.js` |
| DETECT runbook | `scenarios/01-typosquatting/DETECT.md` |
| ES forward hook | `detection-tools/es/forward-capture.js` |
| Scripts / doc sync | `documentation/platform/TOOLING.md` |
| Ports | `scripts/ports.env` |

**Exceptions:** **06** — `credential-harvester.js`, `mock-cdn.js`; **21**/**22** — npm/PyPI sims, **22** uses `mock_server.py`.

Shared-pattern edits: implement in **01** (or exception), `grep` `scenarios/` + `documentation/scenario-guides/`, apply the same diff — do not open all 22 folders.

## Exploration

`grep`/glob before broad reads. Read narrow slices (signatures, call sites). Stop once the pattern is clear.
